text:
I think Im literally the only person that thought this was a terrible post.

He's talking about doing 'discover' type tests (ie where is the biggest signal) and assuming everyone does 'optimization' type tests (double down on the signal once time found it).
It's not an either/or situation, ie go prospecting before you start mining.

The post didn't communicate clearly that you should do both things & in a given order.
The too-cute title didn't help communicate that either. If he'd just said 'Try bigger A/B tests first' (or Try A/J tests first) that would've been more accurate.

I get that Seth is like this marketing philosopher who like to be pithy but sometimes more is more.
